Watford have completed the signing of defender Craig Dawson from West Brom for an undisclosed fee. Centre-back Dawson has agreed a four-year deal at Vicarage Road to become the Premier League club’s first summer signing accoding to express.co.uk. The 29-year-old scored three times in 45 appearances in all competitions for the Baggies last season as they reached the Championship play-off semi-finals. “The club wishes Craig and his family all the very best in the future,” read a statement on West Brom’s website.